# migrated from tests/cases/compare.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test compare]
# gen27: ordinal reasoning over quantities — "is <a> more/less than <b>?".
# Discovered by domain-pull from the first official SuperGLUE/BoolQ question
# ("does ethanol take more energy ... than [it] produces"): comparing two
# magnitudes is a reasoning primitive the symbolic KB lacked.
#
# The decisive case is the ethanol one, reduced to its extracted quantities
# (energy in = 1, energy out = 1.3): "take more than it produces?" -> No,
# which is BoolQ #0's gold label. We test the *reasoning*, not the passage.
> is 1 more than 1.3?
< No.
> is 8 more than 1?
< Yes.
> is 1 less than 1.3?
< Yes.
> is 3 more than 3?
< No.
> is 2.5 greater than 2.49?
< Yes.
> is 4 fewer than 10?
< Yes.
# Non-numbers are declined honestly, not guessed at.
> is five more than apples?
< I don't understand that yet.
